			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>&#8220;The biggest problem with the Austrian school is a legacy of the fact that much (not all!) of the theory was developed before the rational expectations revolution.&#8221;</p>
<p>I couldn&#8217;t agree more! When I was a student, Austrian economic philosophy provided no answers. Adherents are stuck in the past, more intent on criticizing the old &#8220;Anglo&#8221; giants (Smith, Marshall, Keynes, etc.) than the math-heavy theories we were learning in class. As long as they continue to do this, they will continue to be socially irrelevant.</p>
<p>Have to disagree with you on one point though: Austrians, as a rule, are elitist. They often differ on what points &#8211; national heritage, religious heritage, education, music and literature, dress &#8211; but they&#8217;re definitely the snobbiest.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

